TransValue, which specializes in transporting valuable goods and money between financial centers, keeps goods they move insured for up to $100million. 

Its owner Jesus Rodriguez said that neither of the guards were injured during the 'very rare' incident, according to WRAL.

Rodriguez is currently heading to Wilson County, which is about halfway between Miami and eastern Massachusetts.

